How to choose the mattress and spring: women and men look for different things
Nothing of a pompous frame for the bed; what really confers its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, that is, the mattress and the spring.
Above all, they must be perfectly complemented so that they can be adapted to specific users.
During the election numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, health status and sex of the owner.
Also important is the type of interior on which the mattress and the spring are located.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they are "heated" more slowly.
In addition, they often weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
It is therefore necessary to turn them over more frequently.
If the canals of the center are not properly aerated and above, they are on a firm basis, they keep the moisture inside. Even mold can appear below.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence.
Anyone who has spent a lot of time abroad often uses a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling good on a lower, harder surface.
"Almost all the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained that they didn't sleep just as well here."
"For their crushed shoulders, heels and hips they needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
"This type of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes who have long nervous system problems, so they get bad information from the joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in quilted furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italian Magniflex, but also the Czech Tropico brand."
You no longer have to be a NHL player to appreciate the viscoelastic.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
Optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not turn like after a hard match.
He just sleeps better.
Viscoelastic also works as a protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to your height the length of your feet, that is, between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example single rooms, it is recommended at least 120 to 140 cm.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, you can apply a simple standard to calculate the width: when lying face up, you should have your hands comfortably shrugged towards your elbows", advises engineer Helena Prokopová, expert from Cechu čalouník
In double rooms, each one needs its own spring and mattress, so during purchase you have to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the springs at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with spring interiors a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeter are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softens.
"When you touch it with your hand or when you sit on the mattress, the docks should certainly not be noticed," says Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a certain type of spring.
The fully quilted bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
Mattresses breathe badly and you can't wash their cover, which is often done today.
And, since every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a mattress life of up to 25 years or even a lifetime guarantee.
However, everything has a but.
Therefore, sellers give advice: on mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, carefully take care of cleaning and washing the cover, but better add a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Although mattress covers are currently made with zipper closure throughout their perimeter, so when opening them they stay in two parts (something very important for washing and the size of the washing machine!), their handling in larger models (and by a single person) when lifting the mattress may seem like a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a spring, do you have a firm board?
Never!
As much for beds designed for overnight visits.
However, it should make (if you don't already have them) ventilation holes in the board and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-articulating sheet springs containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g. a combination of latex and coconut fiber) may be used, although it is always best to use a spring with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the lumbar area sheets are reinforced and their stiffness can be regulated.
Articulated sheet springs should not be used with a spring mattress, as it does not react to reclining.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
It is a special fixing of the sheets that allows pressing or even tilting the sheets in such a way that they "round" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, this is very important.
They are even remembered by mattress manufacturers who, in the "males", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are spring boxes with cross structure or splints with the so-called multitorsion damping.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the tension is reduced.
You should also keep in mind that even if you use the appropriate mattress and spring, if you use a bad pillow (large and "blow"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow must hold the head and the corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles of them can relax.
The recommended suitable size is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying down on the side, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with the spring with shoulder reinforcement or softer area of the mattress) as the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses seem to have something to do with the original mattresses filled with straw.
Manufacturers continue to use, increasingly, natural materials or, at least, mixtures.
In fact, biological mattresses are fashionable.
Oil-based raw materials, from which polyurethane foam is manufactured, are filled with natural oils, e.g. castor or soy.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soy.
"Biological, in the case of mattresses, means that the centre is made only of materials of natural origin," explains Petr Vašíček of Tropico Plus.
Also, natural substances are used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma to forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men "refresh" with vegetable breeze extracts, so that the mattress cover absorbs heat and refreshes the body, women prefer to "heat" the sheath.
The red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so women feel more warmth.
The favorites these days?
Cold foam mattresses, which are more porous, with an adapted cell structure, make them more permeable than normal polyurethane mattresses and offer more permeability.
The combination of various rigidities of cold foam and viscoelastic make mattresses from different areas that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels are going.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who perform a therapeutic function usually have lower VAT, as they are considered as health facilities.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It is difficult to save on mattresses and springs.
Sometimes offers from manufacturers or sellers can be approved, which sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a memory foam attached to the cover for 11,990 crowns.
The second is obtained free of charge.
The era of viscoelastics with an open cell structure and a high density began with Tempur's "cosmic" material.
Initially it emerged as material for NASA, because during the take-offs astronauts were subject to enormous overload.
Tempur softens with heat and hardens with cold.
Therefore, the human body, warm, exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores, but also to improve comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foam is not only used in mattresses, but also for sanitary products, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
National manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and the like.
More and more parents use tracking devices to control their children
Fear for children is driving more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed to track vehicles, can also follow the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, in the case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old Anička Janatková.
At the moment the device is about the size of a matchbox, but will soon be reduced to the size of a clock.
Many people were afraid of the case of the missing Anička and began to learn about the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
"We are all trying to tell us that it is not a matter of spying, but of another means of reducing the chances of a tragedy," says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they are put in someone's purse without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases."
"Most customers actually buy it for security reasons," Pilin adds.
In their opinion, children should always know what the "box" is for and how it is used in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bočková warns of the fact that if the child does not want to wear it, he will simply throw it away.
"Even younger children show great creativity in intentionally losing certain things if they want to avoid being controlled."
"Before, parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but they could be turned off as easily as the tracking device," says Bočková.
In his opinion, it is questionable whether in case of attack such a device is really useful.
“If it is a prepared kidnapping, the perpetrator will practically always check whether the child has any electronic devices that can reveal his or her location.”
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices expands, you will also look for them, since their sale will certainly be carried out with a lot of publicity."
"In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police," says the psychologist.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised attack by a pedophile.
According to Robert Čech of the RC Monitoring company, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, their presence can help.
"The device can be configured to send the position regularly after a certain period."
"If you suffer damage, at least it will facilitate the last position of the person in question."
"The most expensive devices have a tilt gauge integrated, so if the person simply slips and stays still, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question," says Čech.
In his view, such a service could be obtained even with smart phones with navigation, on which only special software should be installed.
The problem with current tracking units is that for the time being these are devices with a size similar to a matchbox or smaller mobile phones.
They can therefore be lost.
According to Pilin of Macro Weil, this is why testing is currently taking place with devices that look like a digital clock.
"In addition, they will have the added advantage that a potential aggressor may not identify the device."
"Or I.D. him after a while, which can make the police buy time," he adds.
Even if the tracking devices are worn on the wrist or hanging, they will continue to use the same technology used for vehicle tracking.
