They usually stay in motels and park the van right in front of their room window.
They were carrying three other dogs (a boxer's baby, a terrier Parson Russell and a Brittany, who slept with them in the motel room.
But they left the Akitas and Corgis in the van because they had a very thick coat and would be cooler.
They left the windows slightly open so that dogs could breathe fresh air.
Peek and Rickard reported the van stolen Tuesday morning at 6:00 a.m.
